1
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:08,240
Can you take me to see him?

2
00:02:09,159 --> 00:02:10,719
I have to ask him something.

3
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:14,280
Tarn told me
that he wanted Nut to be happy.

4
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:15,960
He wants him to do the job he loves

5
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:18,599
and be surrounded by good people.

6
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:20,719
…You meet someone better than me,

7
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:23,919
someone you are happier with,

8
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:25,960
and isn't a burden like me?

9
00:02:27,919 --> 00:02:29,280
Will you leave me for him?

10
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:30,960
Did you bring me here

11
00:02:32,159 --> 00:02:33,360
for a particular reason?

12
00:02:33,439 --> 00:02:35,599
Each of us is a unique flower.

13
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:37,800
You are a special flower

14
00:02:37,879 --> 00:02:38,960
that belongs to me.

15
00:02:42,080 --> 00:02:43,159
Tofu.

16
00:02:48,599 --> 00:02:50,520
I'm glad I get to love you.

17
00:03:00,159 --> 00:03:01,680
If death parts us one day

18
00:03:03,319 --> 00:03:05,520
and a miracle brings us back together,

19
00:03:08,719 --> 00:03:10,520
would we fall in love again?

20
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:16,759
If I died

21
00:03:18,479 --> 00:03:20,039
and came back as a ghost,

22
00:03:21,319 --> 00:03:22,400
would you run from me?

23
00:03:26,159 --> 00:03:28,039
I wouldn't run even if you were ugly.

24
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:30,000
I see.

25
00:03:30,080 --> 00:03:31,719
I should come back all handsome,

26
00:03:33,199 --> 00:03:34,800
so you would fall for me first.

27
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:43,759
Is something wrong, Nut?

28
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:47,840
I'm fine.

29
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:51,280
To me,

30
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:53,960
the fact that we are together

31
00:03:54,759 --> 00:03:55,879
is a dream come true.

32
00:03:57,719 --> 00:03:59,479
Luck doesn't come by often.

33
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:05,039
You are being too modest.

34
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:07,560
I'm being ambitious.

35
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:12,240
I just don't want us to part ways.

36
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:24,600
What are you doing?

37
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:26,800
Well, I'm taking a photo as proof.

38
00:04:27,279 --> 00:04:29,399
You promised to love me and only me.

39
00:04:30,839 --> 00:04:31,759
Stop it.

40
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:34,920
Stop it, Tarn.

41
00:04:59,279 --> 00:05:00,519
I'm sorry, Nut.

42
00:05:04,199 --> 00:05:05,800
I didn't know how to tell you.

43
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:20,120
The person you recognized…

44
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:24,600
Was it really Tarn?

45
00:05:27,319 --> 00:05:28,319
Yes.

46
00:05:34,639 --> 00:05:35,800
I just found out

47
00:05:36,319 --> 00:05:37,920
that Prib knows him too.

48
00:05:40,160 --> 00:05:41,959
We came here together yesterday.

49
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:45,199
Yesterday?

50
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:51,079
You recognized Tarn.

51
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:54,399
You knew who he was.

52
00:05:56,839 --> 00:05:58,439
Why didn't you tell me?

53
00:06:01,519 --> 00:06:03,879
And you still asked me those questions.

54
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:17,639
You know,

55
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:21,319
I wasn't delighted at all when you said

56
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:24,600
you recognized him.

57
00:06:29,079 --> 00:06:30,040
I was scared.

58
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:37,399
I was scared that if I brought you to him,

59
00:06:39,519 --> 00:06:40,959
I would lose you.

60
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:48,160
But if I held you back,

61
00:06:51,079 --> 00:06:52,160
you would be hurt.

62
00:07:06,759 --> 00:07:08,120
I'm sorry.

63
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:14,759
I hurt your feelings again.

64
00:07:18,399 --> 00:07:19,839
I'm really sorry.

65
00:07:26,519 --> 00:07:28,040
You didn't hurt me.

66
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:35,319
I was just surprised.

67
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:41,720
I thought of him…

68
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:47,439
but I didn't expect to see him
in that condition.

69
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,319
I didn't think

70
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:57,920
that you guys…

71
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,199
would know each other.

72
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:14,600
Aren't you happy

73
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,240
to see him again?

74
00:08:24,920 --> 00:08:25,879
I never thought

75
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:28,720
about how I would feel
if I ever saw him again.

76
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:34,320
But just now,

77
00:08:36,759 --> 00:08:38,039
when I saw him…

78
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:47,600
I realized that he wasn't just…

79
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,039
Just on your mind.

80
00:08:56,519 --> 00:08:57,600
You miss him.

81
00:09:03,919 --> 00:09:05,919
Do you still love Tatarn?

82
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:14,240
I don't know.

83
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:23,879
But I really love you, Tofu.

84
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:36,240
Thank you.

85
00:09:50,039 --> 00:09:51,480
It's really funny.

86
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:56,799
How can the two people I love

87
00:09:58,639 --> 00:09:59,840
know each other?

88
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:06,639
Why did you have to see Tarn?

89
00:10:10,799 --> 00:10:12,799
Why do you know each other?

90
00:10:41,919 --> 00:10:44,080
AN OLD STORY RETOLD…
AFTER A LONG WHILE

91
00:10:53,639 --> 00:10:55,720
Tofu told you all about it, didn't he?

92
00:11:01,519 --> 00:11:02,840
I'm sorry

93
00:11:04,159 --> 00:11:07,240
for causing trouble
and hurting your and Tofu's feelings.

94
00:11:10,759 --> 00:11:13,360
I don't know if a miracle
will happen or not.

95
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:16,080
All I can do is hope.

96
00:11:17,360 --> 00:11:18,799
If a miracle happens,

97
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:21,120
that would be good.

98
00:11:25,039 --> 00:11:26,159
But if it doesn't…

99
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:49,080
Do you still love Tatarn?

100
00:11:52,799 --> 00:11:53,879
I don't know.

101
00:11:56,279 --> 00:11:58,120
But I really love you, Tofu.

102
00:12:22,919 --> 00:12:23,919
Don't worry about it.

103
00:12:24,879 --> 00:12:26,639
They used to date after all.

104
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:28,240
Nut is just showing his support.

105
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:35,240
Mr. Saen.

106
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:36,720
Jan.

107
00:12:55,519 --> 00:12:58,200
I can't believe we all know each other.

108
00:12:59,279 --> 00:13:00,960
People say it's a small world.

109
00:13:01,039 --> 00:13:02,480
Everyone is family.

110
00:13:02,559 --> 00:13:04,600
We are either related by blood

111
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:06,159
or by sex.

112
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:09,480
Stay quiet if you have nothing to say.

113
00:13:09,559 --> 00:13:11,799
I was just making a joke.

114
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:15,279
You came all this way to make a joke.

115
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:17,399
You must have a lot of time on your hands.

116
00:13:17,960 --> 00:13:19,559
Yes, I do.

117
00:13:20,120 --> 00:13:22,720
I went to see Saen
after I collected the rent.

118
00:13:24,039 --> 00:13:26,120
If I had known
you wanted to join our trip,

119
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:28,039
I would have invited you.

120
00:13:29,399 --> 00:13:32,320
A trip with me wouldn't be as fun
as a trip with your gay…

121
00:13:33,279 --> 00:13:36,120
I mean, your family.

122
00:13:36,759 --> 00:13:38,919
Na must be really happy

123
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,559
that her son

124
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:43,200
and his friend took her on a trip.

125
00:13:44,559 --> 00:13:45,480
Yes.

126
00:13:46,399 --> 00:13:48,480
I was going to visit you with my mom.

127
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:51,200
You didn't have much time
to talk last time.

128
00:13:51,759 --> 00:13:54,080
You guys get along really well.

129
00:13:54,159 --> 00:13:55,600
She would be happy to see you.

130
00:13:56,639 --> 00:13:57,600
Right, Tofu?

131
00:13:59,720 --> 00:14:00,600
Yes.

132
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:05,600
Why don't you invite Na over for dinner?

133
00:14:05,679 --> 00:14:07,919
-We can have a long conversation.
-No.

134
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:10,679
I'm sure their schedule is packed.

135
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:13,600
Why not? Are you afraid of something?

136
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:16,399
Don't you want to see an old friend?

137
00:14:17,639 --> 00:14:18,759
Sure.

138
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:22,600
It has been a while
since we ate as a family.

139
00:14:35,879 --> 00:14:37,759
If you and Tofu hadn't visited Tarn,

140
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:40,720
we wouldn't be having
a meal together like this.

141
00:14:44,639 --> 00:14:46,039
Did you say Tarn?

142
00:14:49,039 --> 00:14:50,799
Tarn, the guy Tofu recognized,

143
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:52,559
is Jan's nephew.

144
00:14:54,639 --> 00:14:57,360
I don't know how close Tarn and Tofu were.

145
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:58,879
I hope

146
00:14:58,960 --> 00:15:00,679
it is not what I think it is.

147
00:15:09,759 --> 00:15:10,679
Everyone.

148
00:15:10,759 --> 00:15:12,159
The food is here.

149
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:14,480
Let's all eat.

150
00:15:14,559 --> 00:15:16,200
The food here is great.

151
00:15:16,279 --> 00:15:17,759
My dad takes me here often.

152
00:15:19,279 --> 00:15:20,759
Jan, do you happen to know

153
00:15:22,399 --> 00:15:23,759
how close

154
00:15:25,279 --> 00:15:26,600
Tarn and I were?

155
00:15:32,559 --> 00:15:34,120
I don't know.

156
00:15:34,960 --> 00:15:36,759
If I had known you,

157
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:39,080
I would have recognized you
from the beginning.

158
00:15:39,159 --> 00:15:42,360
Tarn's mouth often got him in trouble,

159
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:43,840
so we weren't really close.

160
00:15:44,440 --> 00:15:45,559
All I remember is

161
00:15:45,639 --> 00:15:48,039
when he was in high school in Bangkok,

162
00:15:48,120 --> 00:15:50,759
he got called into the principal's office.

163
00:15:51,399 --> 00:15:54,480
I don't know what happened back then.

164
00:15:54,559 --> 00:15:56,000
But I kind of

165
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:57,120
have an idea now.

166
00:15:58,960 --> 00:16:01,159
I wonder whose toes
he stepped on this time.

167
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:02,600
That person put him in a coma.

168
00:16:04,559 --> 00:16:06,720
We'll have to wait for him to wake up

169
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:09,240
to find out whose toes he stepped on.

170
00:16:12,159 --> 00:16:13,480
Tarn wouldn't get involved

171
00:16:14,759 --> 00:16:16,000
for no reason.

172
00:16:17,519 --> 00:16:19,879
You seem to know a lot about him.

173
00:16:19,960 --> 00:16:21,320
You must have been close.

174
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:24,320
If that's true,

175
00:16:24,399 --> 00:16:26,480
I hope someone here doesn't mind.

176
00:16:28,159 --> 00:16:29,840
It's none of your business.

177
00:16:30,559 --> 00:16:31,639
Just eat.

178
00:16:34,879 --> 00:16:36,759
Tarn and I used to be close.

179
00:16:38,720 --> 00:16:40,399
We were a couple.

180
00:16:48,960 --> 00:16:49,879
But right now,

181
00:16:50,679 --> 00:16:51,879
Tofu and I

182
00:16:52,679 --> 00:16:53,759
are a couple.

183
00:16:56,399 --> 00:16:57,799
You finally came out.

184
00:17:01,399 --> 00:17:04,000
Actually, I don't feel
the need to announce

185
00:17:04,079 --> 00:17:05,240
what I am

186
00:17:05,319 --> 00:17:06,440
and who I'm dating.

187
00:17:07,559 --> 00:17:09,000
But if you really want to know,

188
00:17:09,559 --> 00:17:10,440
I can tell you.

189
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:14,400
It's not something
to be embarrassed about.

190
00:17:15,880 --> 00:17:17,839
We are just like a heterosexual couple.

191
00:17:19,119 --> 00:17:20,319
We live in the same house,

192
00:17:20,920 --> 00:17:22,000
spend time together,

193
00:17:23,119 --> 00:17:24,200
and sleep together.

194
00:17:26,720 --> 00:17:28,599
I think it's more embarrassing

195
00:17:29,319 --> 00:17:31,200
to pretend to have a perfect relationship

196
00:17:33,119 --> 00:17:34,720
when it's far from the truth.

197
00:17:38,359 --> 00:17:39,680
I'm surprised

198
00:17:39,759 --> 00:17:41,599
at how honest you're being.

199
00:17:44,119 --> 00:17:45,799
The fact that you're okay with this

200
00:17:45,880 --> 00:17:47,920
proves you are quite ignorant.

201
00:17:50,160 --> 00:17:52,240
That's not true.

202
00:17:52,799 --> 00:17:53,720
The ignorant one

203
00:17:54,519 --> 00:17:56,279
is the person judging other people.

204
00:17:56,359 --> 00:17:59,039
Is it wrong that some people
can't accept it?

205
00:17:59,119 --> 00:18:00,440
No, it's not.

206
00:18:01,319 --> 00:18:03,079
Whether someone can accept it or not,

207
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:04,119
it's their problem.

208
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:05,920
Everyone has rights.

209
00:18:07,240 --> 00:18:08,519
I just realized

210
00:18:08,599 --> 00:18:10,240
that you're not just a screenwriter,

211
00:18:10,319 --> 00:18:12,559
but you are a human rights activist too.

212
00:18:14,279 --> 00:18:16,599
Anyone can show interest in human rights.

213
00:18:16,680 --> 00:18:18,720
It's up to us whether we care or not.

214
00:18:19,720 --> 00:18:23,079
People have been paying attention

215
00:18:23,160 --> 00:18:24,880
to human rights and equality.

216
00:18:25,720 --> 00:18:27,960
You don't have to be an LGBTQ+

217
00:18:28,039 --> 00:18:31,519
in order to fight for their rights.

218
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:34,279
You don't have to be a disabled person

219
00:18:34,359 --> 00:18:37,039
in order to fight for their rights.

220
00:18:38,119 --> 00:18:39,359
Your voice

221
00:18:39,440 --> 00:18:40,880
can help other people.

222
00:18:41,880 --> 00:18:45,680
I understand you need principle and reason
to talk to kids these days.

223
00:18:45,759 --> 00:18:47,640
I might be old-fashioned,

224
00:18:47,720 --> 00:18:50,039
but I will try to understand
your point of view.

225
00:18:50,559 --> 00:18:51,799
People from my days

226
00:18:51,880 --> 00:18:55,160
would call you guys "faggots,"

227
00:18:55,960 --> 00:18:58,119
but people nowadays would probably say

228
00:18:58,599 --> 00:19:00,519
you are just two people in love.

229
00:19:00,599 --> 00:19:01,519
A genderless love.

230
00:19:01,599 --> 00:19:03,680
Something like that, right?

231
00:19:05,599 --> 00:19:07,480
Everybody has a gender.

232
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:10,119
You can be any gender you wish to be.

233
00:19:10,759 --> 00:19:13,160
And every gender is equal.

234
00:19:14,240 --> 00:19:16,559
The term "genderless love"

235
00:19:16,640 --> 00:19:18,640
might sound romantic to you,

236
00:19:19,279 --> 00:19:23,200
but it shows how
you do not accept our identities.

237
00:19:25,039 --> 00:19:26,559
Specifying one's gender

238
00:19:26,640 --> 00:19:29,000
is a way to show respect.

239
00:19:32,079 --> 00:19:33,960
If you still don't get it,

240
00:19:34,039 --> 00:19:35,960
I would be happy to explain it

241
00:19:36,039 --> 00:19:37,039
when you are free.

242
00:19:37,720 --> 00:19:39,079
There are many things

243
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:41,079
we need to discuss.

244
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:42,240
Got it?

245
00:19:43,319 --> 00:19:44,160
Sajjaree.

246
00:19:44,720 --> 00:19:46,119
Stop it, Jan.

247
00:19:48,559 --> 00:19:49,759
-What?
-Come with me.

248
00:19:50,279 --> 00:19:51,200
What is it?

249
00:20:00,319 --> 00:20:01,559
I'm going to the toilet.

250
00:20:03,640 --> 00:20:05,319
I'll go with you.

251
00:20:06,079 --> 00:20:06,920
It's okay.

252
00:20:07,519 --> 00:20:09,640
I can go alone. Please enjoy the meal.

253
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:27,480
This family gathering

254
00:20:27,960 --> 00:20:29,480
is so damn heartwarming.

255
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:40,319
What is it? Let me go.

256
00:20:40,400 --> 00:20:41,400
Stop it.

257
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:45,680
-Listen.
-Let go.

258
00:20:45,759 --> 00:20:47,359
Why did you do that?

259
00:20:47,440 --> 00:20:48,960
Do what?

260
00:20:49,039 --> 00:20:51,160
You asked Nut about his personal life

261
00:20:51,240 --> 00:20:52,599
and made him uncomfortable.

262
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:54,799
What good did it do?

263
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:56,599
Did it make your life better?

264
00:20:56,680 --> 00:20:59,559
-They were rude to me first.
-Stop it.

265
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:01,000
Don't be silly.

266
00:21:01,079 --> 00:21:03,960
You invited them to scold you.

267
00:21:04,039 --> 00:21:05,720
-So why are you upset?
-Saen.

268
00:21:05,799 --> 00:21:08,319
Do you think I don't know why you're here?

269
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:11,519
Enough with the stupid jealousy.

270
00:21:11,599 --> 00:21:12,680
It's embarrassing.

271
00:21:14,200 --> 00:21:16,039
If you can't do it for your sake,

272
00:21:16,119 --> 00:21:18,799
then do it for the sake
of your so-called husband.

273
00:21:37,279 --> 00:21:38,240
Aren't you hungry?

274
00:21:38,839 --> 00:21:40,200
You keep staring at the food.

275
00:21:41,759 --> 00:21:44,279
We are at a very famous restaurant.

276
00:21:44,359 --> 00:21:46,319
We can't just sit here.

277
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:48,519
All right, I'll start the meal.

278
00:21:49,799 --> 00:21:51,119
You guys go ahead and eat.

279
00:21:51,920 --> 00:21:53,200
I'm going to check on Mom.

280
00:21:53,839 --> 00:21:54,720
Nut.

281
00:22:01,759 --> 00:22:03,000
Wait.

282
00:22:32,960 --> 00:22:33,880
Nut.

