you are smiling.

567
00:46:01,639 --> 00:46:02,840
Sometimes, I wonder

568
00:46:03,840 --> 00:46:04,800
where you came from.

569
00:46:06,239 --> 00:46:07,920
How can you warm my heart this much?

570
00:46:14,840 --> 00:46:16,519
Your family raised you well.

571
00:46:20,400 --> 00:46:21,400
Who knows,

572
00:46:22,239 --> 00:46:24,320
maybe I came from another planet.

573
00:46:26,280 --> 00:46:27,599
Even your mom said

574
00:46:28,440 --> 00:46:30,840
I'm a Little Prince who fell from the sky.

575
00:46:32,360 --> 00:46:33,599
You can't believe her.

576
00:46:41,320 --> 00:46:43,320
Although you haven't gotten
your memory back,

577
00:46:45,320 --> 00:46:46,320
don't worry.

578
00:46:47,920 --> 00:46:49,840
I'll help you find your family.

579
00:46:54,760 --> 00:46:56,159
Will you let me stay with you

580
00:46:58,719 --> 00:47:00,559
if I don't want to leave?

581
00:47:10,119 --> 00:47:11,559
When you get your memory back,

582
00:47:13,800 --> 00:47:16,320
you might be able to get by without me.

583
00:47:31,239 --> 00:47:32,559
Don't sulk.

584
00:47:33,519 --> 00:47:34,639
I'll help you.

585
00:47:37,639 --> 00:47:39,159
I'm curious.

586
00:47:39,239 --> 00:47:40,880
If you and Tarn

587
00:47:40,960 --> 00:47:41,960
weren't an item,

588
00:47:44,639 --> 00:47:45,719
then how were you

589
00:47:46,960 --> 00:47:47,960
connected?

590
00:48:41,119 --> 00:48:43,039
If you really knew Tarn,

591
00:48:43,599 --> 00:48:44,840
maybe you came here.

592
00:48:46,679 --> 00:48:48,119
Something here

593
00:48:48,760 --> 00:48:50,199
might trigger your memory.

594
00:48:54,679 --> 00:48:55,559
Let's go inside.

595
00:49:21,880 --> 00:49:24,039
This is the first time
I'm learning about you

596
00:49:25,039 --> 00:49:26,440
from your place.

597
00:50:19,119 --> 00:50:20,280
No wonder

598
00:50:21,119 --> 00:50:23,760
you've been in Nut's heart all this time.

599
00:50:53,079 --> 00:50:54,000
Do you like it?

600
00:50:54,800 --> 00:50:55,960
It's cute.

601
00:50:58,960 --> 00:50:59,840
Like you.

602
00:51:03,519 --> 00:51:04,880
How is it like me?

603
00:51:06,559 --> 00:51:07,920
Well,

604
00:51:08,599 --> 00:51:10,199
you're covered in spines,

605
00:51:10,679 --> 00:51:12,519
always protecting yourself.

606
00:51:13,599 --> 00:51:15,320
You can endure extreme conditions,

607
00:51:16,360 --> 00:51:17,679
but deep down,

608
00:51:18,639 --> 00:51:20,719
you need someone to take care of you.

609
00:51:24,519 --> 00:51:25,559
Aren't you afraid

610
00:51:26,400 --> 00:51:27,400
of the spines?

611
00:51:28,639 --> 00:51:29,559
No.

612
00:51:30,639 --> 00:51:31,679
Despite the spines,

613
00:51:32,320 --> 00:51:33,440
you're still cute.

614
00:52:18,239 --> 00:52:19,719
When I found that photo,

615
00:52:21,559 --> 00:52:23,679
I took a picture of it,

616
00:52:23,760 --> 00:52:26,119
hoping to find Tarn's first love.

617
00:52:30,440 --> 00:52:33,719
Tarn often told me about his first love,

618
00:52:34,239 --> 00:52:35,960
but he never said who it was.

619
00:52:38,920 --> 00:52:41,440
Tarn probably didn't want to trouble you.

620
00:52:44,280 --> 00:52:46,079
It made Tarn happy

621
00:52:46,559 --> 00:52:48,559
to see you happy.

622
00:52:52,159 --> 00:52:53,119
What are you doing?

623
00:52:53,760 --> 00:52:55,639
Well, I'm taking a photo as proof.

624
00:52:56,199 --> 00:52:57,880
You promised to love me and only me.

625
00:52:58,800 --> 00:53:00,480
Stop it.

626
00:53:06,320 --> 00:53:07,239
Prib.

627
00:53:08,719 --> 00:53:10,480
Can you take me to Tarn's bedroom?

628
00:53:50,519 --> 00:53:51,719
I used to envy you.

629
00:53:52,519 --> 00:53:55,079
But I promise to envy you less.

630
00:53:56,159 --> 00:53:57,880
I want you to wake up soon.

631
00:53:59,360 --> 00:54:01,280
I can't bear seeing Nut sad anymore.

632
00:54:03,159 --> 00:54:04,679
I'm dying to know

633
00:54:05,320 --> 00:54:07,760
how a teddy bear like me
turned into a human.

634
00:54:16,440 --> 00:54:18,519
Did you say a teddy bear
turned into a human?

635
00:54:21,119 --> 00:54:22,800
Who's talking to me?

636
00:54:24,760 --> 00:54:27,840
Did a teddy bear really turn into a human?

637
00:54:31,079 --> 00:54:33,280
How is that possible?

638
00:54:33,360 --> 00:54:34,519
It's true.

639
00:54:35,599 --> 00:54:37,639
I don't know how it happened.

640
00:54:38,960 --> 00:54:40,960
I think it has something
to do with Tatarn.

641
00:54:41,840 --> 00:54:43,239
Tarn?

642
00:54:43,800 --> 00:54:44,880
Yes.

643
00:54:46,440 --> 00:54:48,679
But he can't tell me anything right now

644
00:54:50,239 --> 00:54:51,760
because he was assaulted.

645
00:54:54,480 --> 00:54:55,960
Do you happen to know

646
00:54:56,039 --> 00:54:57,480
what happened to him?

647
00:55:00,360 --> 00:55:02,320
The incident happened here.

648
00:55:03,519 --> 00:55:04,639
Here?

649
00:55:06,760 --> 00:55:08,280
Did you see the attacker?

650
00:55:08,360 --> 00:55:09,880
I didn't see anyone.

651
00:55:10,440 --> 00:55:12,119
But I heard Tatarn

652
00:55:12,199 --> 00:55:13,880
arguing with a man.

653
00:55:14,360 --> 00:55:15,760
I'm not going to back down.

654
00:55:27,760 --> 00:55:29,679
I heard a vase shatter.

655
00:55:31,760 --> 00:55:34,440
Then I heard a lot of people
coming inside the house

656
00:55:35,840 --> 00:55:37,840
before everything fell quiet.

657
00:55:41,679 --> 00:55:43,639
I don't know who they were.

658
00:55:44,360 --> 00:55:46,679
The last person who came
to clean up the scene

659
00:55:47,679 --> 00:55:48,960
missed a spot.

660
00:55:52,360 --> 00:55:53,559
What do you mean?

661
00:56:21,280 --> 00:56:22,239
It's from the vase.

662
00:56:27,599 --> 00:56:28,920
Did the attacker

663
00:56:29,000 --> 00:56:31,039
hit Tatarn in the head with the vase?

664
00:56:31,599 --> 00:56:33,519
I'm not sure.

665
00:56:33,599 --> 00:56:36,760
But I'm certain that the last person

666
00:56:37,360 --> 00:56:38,760
who came inside

667
00:56:38,840 --> 00:56:40,280
was a woman.

668
00:56:43,159 --> 00:56:44,039
A woman?

669
00:56:45,000 --> 00:56:47,360
Is anyone inside the house?
Come out this instant.

670
00:56:49,960 --> 00:56:51,519
It's her.

671
00:56:51,599 --> 00:56:52,559
It was her voice.

672
00:56:53,840 --> 00:56:54,760
What did you say?

673
00:56:58,320 --> 00:56:59,360
You…

674
00:56:59,440 --> 00:57:00,840
What are you doing here?

675
00:57:00,920 --> 00:57:02,239
Who gave you permission?

676
00:57:04,360 --> 00:57:05,719
I did.

677
00:57:07,639 --> 00:57:08,719
Saen.

678
00:57:13,440 --> 00:57:14,559
Thank you for letting me

679
00:57:15,880 --> 00:57:17,599
bring Tofu here, Uncle Saen.

680
00:57:18,599 --> 00:57:19,719
You are welcome.

681
00:57:20,280 --> 00:57:21,519
Mr. Anik called me.

682
00:57:22,760 --> 00:57:24,400
It's a shame we can't help Tofu.

683
00:57:25,000 --> 00:57:27,079
There's no link between Tofu and Tatarn.

684
00:57:27,840 --> 00:57:28,880
You made up a theory

685
00:57:28,960 --> 00:57:30,880
and came to search someone's house

686
00:57:30,960 --> 00:57:33,000
when the owner's relative
doesn't welcome you.

687
00:57:33,639 --> 00:57:35,079
Why don't you want us here?

688
00:57:35,840 --> 00:57:37,039
This house is beautiful.

689
00:57:38,039 --> 00:57:39,960
Are you hiding something from us?

690
00:57:43,760 --> 00:57:46,719
This house is full of expensive artwork.

691
00:57:46,800 --> 00:57:48,760
I'm Tarn's only relative.

692
00:57:48,840 --> 00:57:50,039
With him in the hospital,

693
00:57:50,119 --> 00:57:52,159
Saen and I need
to watch this house for him.

694
00:57:52,239 --> 00:57:54,960
I will be held responsible
if anything goes missing.

695
00:57:57,440 --> 00:57:58,800
Did you agree to look after it

696
00:57:59,440 --> 00:58:00,519
to offer help

697
00:58:01,480 --> 00:58:02,840
or for something in return?

698
00:58:03,960 --> 00:58:05,280
Nut.

699
00:58:06,559 --> 00:58:07,920
Isn't your mom at the hotel?

700
00:58:08,840 --> 00:58:09,960
You should check on her.

701
00:58:10,039 --> 00:58:11,239
I'll lock up the house.

702
00:58:11,320 --> 00:58:12,840
We should go

703
00:58:12,920 --> 00:58:14,480
before something goes missing.

704
00:58:15,199 --> 00:58:16,480
Hey.

705
00:58:17,599 --> 00:58:19,199
-Listen to her.
-Stop.

706
00:58:23,559 --> 00:58:24,920
Teddy.

707
00:58:26,000 --> 00:58:28,840
The voices I heard that day

708
00:58:28,920 --> 00:58:30,639
belong to these two people.

709
00:58:33,960 --> 00:58:36,920
You must find Tarn's attackers.

710
00:59:01,599 --> 00:59:03,519
How could you let them inside the house?

711
00:59:04,599 --> 00:59:05,599
I had no choice.

712
00:59:06,079 --> 00:59:07,880
The officer called to ask for a favor.

713
00:59:07,960 --> 00:59:09,599
I couldn't trigger his suspicion.

714
00:59:09,679 --> 00:59:12,519
Did you see the way
they were looking at us?

715
00:59:13,039 --> 00:59:13,920
Do you really think

716
00:59:14,000 --> 00:59:16,400
they came here to get Tofu's memory back?

717
00:59:38,519 --> 00:59:41,519
TATARN KLAIANANT

718
00:59:41,599 --> 00:59:45,639
AN ARTIST WHOSE VOICE IS HEARD THROUGH ART

719
00:59:46,719 --> 00:59:48,360
Tarn, the guy Tofu recognized,

720
00:59:49,000 --> 00:59:50,079
is Jan's nephew.

721
00:59:51,559 --> 00:59:52,719
My name is Tatarn.

722
00:59:53,440 --> 00:59:54,960
I just came back from Japan.

723
00:59:56,000 --> 00:59:57,000
Tatarn…

724
01:00:10,039 --> 01:00:10,920
Mom.

725
01:00:12,519 --> 01:00:13,519
Is something wrong?

726
01:00:20,119 --> 01:00:21,079
No.

727
01:00:25,559 --> 01:00:26,559
Are you free later?

728
01:00:28,960 --> 01:00:30,079
Where do you want to go?

729
01:00:31,039 --> 01:00:32,280
I want to visit him.

730
01:01:13,480 --> 01:01:14,599
Who are you here to see?

731
01:01:14,679 --> 01:01:15,920
Hello.

732
01:01:17,280 --> 01:01:18,559
I'm here to see Nut.

733
01:01:21,440 --> 01:01:22,559
-Thank you.
-No problem.

734
01:01:26,239 --> 01:01:27,880
It's a shame Nut is out of town.

735
01:01:28,960 --> 01:01:30,599
You came here for nothing.

736
01:01:30,679 --> 01:01:31,960
It's fine.

737
01:01:32,559 --> 01:01:34,800
I thought you were my student.

738
01:01:35,719 --> 01:01:37,000
Are you Nut's friend?

739
01:01:37,079 --> 01:01:38,519
Yes.

740
01:01:39,079 --> 01:01:40,639
What's your name?

741
01:01:43,880 --> 01:01:44,719
My name is Tatarn.

742
01:01:45,960 --> 01:01:47,159
I've returned from Japan.

743
01:01:47,239 --> 01:01:49,159
I heard Nut moved here.

744
01:01:49,239 --> 01:01:51,320
I have something to give him.

745
01:01:54,760 --> 01:01:55,599
Here it is.

746
01:01:57,039 --> 01:01:57,880
I drew it myself.

747
01:01:57,960 --> 01:01:59,239
-Really?
-Yes.

748
01:02:07,199 --> 01:02:09,079
Wow, it's adorable.

749
01:02:11,559 --> 01:02:14,760
IT'S NICE TO HAVE SOMEONE BY YOUR SIDE

750
01:02:15,519 --> 01:02:18,719
"It's nice to have someone by your side."

751
01:02:20,960 --> 01:02:21,800
Right, honey?

752
01:02:27,079 --> 01:02:29,239
I'll give this to Nut

753
01:02:29,320 --> 01:02:30,400
when he returns.

754
01:02:31,679 --> 01:02:32,719
Thank you so much.

755
01:02:37,000 --> 01:02:37,920
By the way,

756
01:02:38,599 --> 01:02:40,159
are you here alone?

757
01:02:40,239 --> 01:02:41,960
What are you talking about?

758
01:02:42,039 --> 01:02:44,800
I'm here with Nut's father

759
01:02:44,880 --> 01:02:46,599
and Kuenchai.

760
01:02:54,639 --> 01:02:55,760
Nut's father?

761
01:03:02,199 --> 01:03:03,079
Mom.

762
01:03:05,119 --> 01:03:07,000
Why did you want to see Tarn?

763
01:03:11,320 --> 01:03:12,880
He came to our house.

764
01:03:18,159 --> 01:03:19,159
When?

765
01:03:24,440 --> 01:03:25,920
I don't remember.

766
01:03:27,760 --> 01:03:29,840
But it was after we moved
to the new house.

767
01:03:33,480 --> 01:03:34,880
He brought

768
01:03:36,199 --> 01:03:37,119
the book…

769
01:03:40,320 --> 01:03:41,519
Your favorite book.

770
01:03:43,639 --> 01:03:44,679
He brought it for you.

771
01:03:48,960 --> 01:03:50,000
Kuenchai.

772
01:03:50,559 --> 01:03:52,280
I've got snacks.

773
01:03:52,360 --> 01:03:53,639
Do you want some?

774
01:03:53,719 --> 01:03:54,960
Do you want some? Come.

775
01:03:55,800 --> 01:03:57,039
Show me a jump.

776
01:03:57,119 --> 01:03:58,039
Jump for me.

777
01:03:58,679 --> 01:04:00,599
Jump!

778
01:04:00,679 --> 01:04:01,679
Jump! Oh, no.

779
01:04:01,760 --> 01:04:03,280
-No.
-Hey.

780
01:04:03,360 --> 01:04:04,199
-Oh, no.
-Gosh.

781
01:04:05,320 --> 01:04:06,519
That was a pounce. Oops.

782
01:04:32,159 --> 01:04:33,320
Is this your book?

783
01:04:34,159 --> 01:04:35,000
What?

784
01:04:35,679 --> 01:04:36,679
It's yours.

785
01:04:38,480 --> 01:04:39,719
This isn't mine.

786
01:04:40,679 --> 01:04:42,079
It's yours.

787
01:04:42,880 --> 01:04:44,000
You should put it away.

788
01:05:06,639 --> 01:05:08,599
THE PERSON WHO ALWAYS LOOKS AT YOU

789
01:05:10,920 --> 01:05:11,920
THANK YOU

790
01:05:12,000 --> 01:05:14,960
EVERY DAY WITH YOU

791
01:05:15,039 --> 01:05:19,840
I'VE NEVER FORGOTTEN OUR DAYS TOGETHER

792
01:05:19,920 --> 01:05:24,360
THANK YOU

793
01:05:45,159 --> 01:05:47,519
Tarn brought me that book.

794
01:05:48,320 --> 01:05:50,039
Why didn't you tell me?

795
01:05:52,119 --> 01:05:54,119
You always forget the important stuff.

796
01:05:58,039 --> 01:05:59,159
I've been sick.

797
01:06:01,239 --> 01:06:03,239
I don't remember who gave you the book.

798
01:06:08,159 --> 01:06:11,320
You weren't around much back then,
so I forgot.

799
01:06:13,920 --> 01:06:15,119
I'm sorry.

800
01:06:15,960 --> 01:06:16,960
Nut.

801
01:06:20,800 --> 01:06:22,159
If you leave now,

802
01:06:23,480 --> 01:06:25,119
you'll hurt her feelings.

803
01:06:28,000 --> 01:06:29,639
Don't you think I'm hurt too?

804
01:06:34,519 --> 01:06:35,800
I know you're hurt as well.

805
01:06:51,679 --> 01:06:52,599
You should know

806
01:06:53,079 --> 01:06:54,760
how disappointed,

807
01:06:54,840 --> 01:06:55,880
sad,

808
01:06:55,960 --> 01:06:56,880
and upset I am.

809
01:06:59,519 --> 01:07:01,639
But I'm angrier at my fate than my mom.

810
01:07:03,239 --> 01:07:05,119
How would my life be like

811
01:07:06,119 --> 01:07:07,039
if she had told me?

812
01:07:09,119 --> 01:07:10,760
Nut would be really happy

813
01:07:12,679 --> 01:07:15,119
to have Tatarn next to him now,

814
01:07:17,119 --> 01:07:18,079
instead of me.

815
01:07:19,559 --> 01:07:21,360
No one knows

816
01:07:21,440 --> 01:07:23,360
whether you would be happy or sad.

817
01:07:24,079 --> 01:07:25,400
You might think

818
01:07:25,480 --> 01:07:27,280
that you guys would be together now.

819
01:07:27,920 --> 01:07:29,039
But don't forget

820
01:07:29,119 --> 01:07:31,039
your mom was sick,
and she was conservative

821
01:07:31,639 --> 01:07:32,760
two years ago.

822
01:07:33,239 --> 01:07:35,519
Your relationship with Tarn
would be a secret

823
01:07:35,599 --> 01:07:37,639
unlike your relationship with Tofu now.

824
01:07:40,280 --> 01:07:41,239
Tofu.

825
01:07:41,960 --> 01:07:45,000
Everything requires good timing.

826
01:07:45,920 --> 01:07:47,360
Two years ago,

827
01:07:47,440 --> 01:07:49,039
Tarn's timing was wrong.

828
01:07:49,119 --> 01:07:50,360
That's why they broke up.

829
01:07:52,360 --> 01:07:53,639
On the other hand,

830
01:07:53,719 --> 01:07:56,039
you walked into Nut's life
at the perfect time.

831
01:07:58,599 --> 01:08:00,599
But Tatarn is back in the picture now.

832
01:08:02,920 --> 01:08:05,400
Is it possible that
this is the right timing

833
01:08:07,480 --> 01:08:08,639
for them to reunite?

834
01:08:10,440 --> 01:08:12,079
Being afraid of the future

835
01:08:12,159 --> 01:08:15,639
is as bad as wanting to fix the past.

836
01:08:16,199 --> 01:08:17,199
You should live

837
01:08:18,159 --> 01:08:19,399
in the present.

838
01:08:20,000 --> 01:08:23,199
You should use the time to worry
about your loved ones' feelings.

839
01:08:24,000 --> 01:08:25,399
You are confusing Tofu

840
01:08:26,119 --> 01:08:29,199
by expressing countless concerns
toward your ex-boyfriend.

841
01:08:52,800 --> 01:08:53,800
I was looking for you.

842
01:08:56,079 --> 01:08:57,479
Me too.

843
01:09:00,439 --> 01:09:01,760
I know

844
01:09:01,840 --> 01:09:03,279
it's hard to accept

845
01:09:04,359 --> 01:09:06,520
that you had almost crossed paths with him

846
01:09:07,960 --> 01:09:09,880
and could have gotten back together,

847
01:09:12,039 --> 01:09:14,039
but your sick mom took away the chance.

848
01:09:16,880 --> 01:09:18,239
I don't mind the situation.

849
01:09:19,840 --> 01:09:21,119
I'm just regretful.

850
01:09:22,000 --> 01:09:23,520
If I had met him back then,

851
01:09:24,279 --> 01:09:25,640
I could have apologized.

852
01:09:27,359 --> 01:09:28,279
But now,

853
01:09:29,439 --> 01:09:31,279
I might not get a chance to apologize.

854
01:09:32,680 --> 01:09:34,279
He might not wake up

855
01:09:36,760 --> 01:09:38,319
to watch the series I produced.

856
01:09:41,720 --> 01:09:43,640
I'm sure he's going to wake up.

857
01:09:44,960 --> 01:09:46,560
You worked really hard on it.

858
01:09:47,560 --> 01:09:48,640
Who knows,

859
01:09:49,560 --> 01:09:51,840
a miracle might happen.

860
01:09:58,159 --> 01:09:59,119
Give me a hug.

861
01:10:09,319 --> 01:10:10,199
Are you hungry?

862
01:10:11,359 --> 01:10:12,600
My stomach didn't growl.

863
01:10:13,279 --> 01:10:14,239
It wasn't mine.

864
01:10:18,039 --> 01:10:19,319
It was mine.

865
01:10:20,279 --> 01:10:21,960
-You.
-Hey.

866
01:10:22,039 --> 01:10:24,840
Your stomach growled really loud.
Why don't you eat something?

867
01:10:24,920 --> 01:10:26,239
Wait.

868
01:10:26,319 --> 01:10:28,560
Didn't we just eat?

869
01:10:30,560 --> 01:10:33,479
It took a lot of energy to get them

870
01:10:33,560 --> 01:10:35,239
to make up.

871
01:10:36,399 --> 01:10:37,800
Shall we go eat?

872
01:10:38,720 --> 01:10:39,640
-Yes.
-Let's go.

873
01:10:44,960 --> 01:10:46,000
Let me get my mom.

874
01:10:46,079 --> 01:10:48,039
This meal is on Nut then.

875
01:10:48,119 --> 01:10:51,159
He made up with his boyfriend after all.

876
01:10:51,239 --> 01:10:53,479
-Yes!
-Yes!

877
01:10:53,560 --> 01:10:54,960
Yes!

878
01:10:55,720 --> 01:10:57,000
-Let's go, Tofu.
-All right.

879
01:10:57,680 --> 01:10:59,840
We're getting a free meal. Let's go.

880
01:11:00,359 --> 01:11:01,520
Come on.

881
01:11:09,880 --> 01:11:10,760
Mom.

882
01:11:12,520 --> 01:11:13,479
Mom.

883
01:11:14,159 --> 01:11:15,119
Let's grab some food.

884
01:11:17,359 --> 01:11:18,279
Mrs. Na.

885
01:11:22,239 --> 01:11:23,119
Mom.

886
01:11:26,920 --> 01:11:27,760
Mom.

887
01:11:28,279 --> 01:11:29,479
Let's eat.

888
01:11:29,560 --> 01:11:30,520
Mrs. Na.

889
01:11:36,920 --> 01:11:37,760
Mom.

890
01:11:38,359 --> 01:11:39,319
Mrs. Na.

891
01:11:43,640 --> 01:11:44,560
Mom.

892
01:11:48,199 --> 01:11:49,119
Mom.

893
01:11:51,800 --> 01:11:52,720
Nut.

894
01:12:21,239 --> 01:12:23,079
-Gen, have you seen my mom?
-What?

895
01:12:23,159 --> 01:12:24,840
-Your mom?
-She's missing.

896
01:12:26,720 --> 01:12:28,039
Nut.

897
01:12:31,039 --> 01:12:31,880
Nut.

898
01:12:32,479 --> 01:12:34,000
-I'll check the front.
-Okay.

899
01:12:34,079 --> 01:12:34,960
See you.

900
01:12:35,039 --> 01:12:36,199
-Excuse me.
-Yes.

901
01:12:36,279 --> 01:12:38,039
Have you seen the guest from Room 202?

902
01:12:38,119 --> 01:12:39,640
She's tall and thin.

903
01:12:39,720 --> 01:12:40,880
Around 50 years old.

904
01:12:41,439 --> 01:12:43,640
She's wearing a blue shirt
with grey pants.

905
01:12:44,600 --> 01:12:47,199
Yes, she left the hotel
about half an hour ago.

906
01:12:47,279 --> 01:12:48,840
Can we help you with anything?

907
01:12:49,960 --> 01:12:51,840
Can you check the security footage?

908
01:12:51,920 --> 01:12:52,880
Of course.

909
01:13:05,119 --> 01:13:06,119
How did it go?

910
01:13:06,199 --> 01:13:07,960
She walked out by herself

911
01:13:08,039 --> 01:13:09,439
without her wallet or phone.

912
01:13:10,720 --> 01:13:12,079
Where did she go?

913
01:13:13,439 --> 01:13:16,159
Maybe she's taking a walk.

914
01:13:18,520 --> 01:13:20,079
Is she that mad at me?

915
01:13:20,159 --> 01:13:22,680
Maybe she wants to be alone
to think things over.

916
01:13:22,760 --> 01:13:24,359
Calm down.

917
01:13:24,920 --> 01:13:26,640
How about we look for her?

918
01:13:27,319 --> 01:13:28,680
I told the hotel to call us

919
01:13:28,760 --> 01:13:30,279
if she comes back.

920
01:13:31,159 --> 01:13:32,560
She just left.

921
01:13:32,640 --> 01:13:34,079
She couldn't have gone far.

922
01:13:34,159 --> 01:13:36,960
We should look for her in the city.

923
01:13:38,039 --> 01:13:38,880
Let's go.

924
01:13:38,960 --> 01:13:40,199
Come on.

925
01:13:40,279 --> 01:13:41,119
Come, Tofu.

926
01:16:09,640 --> 01:16:10,520
Excuse me.

927
01:16:11,119 --> 01:16:12,439
Have you seen this woman?

928
01:16:13,840 --> 01:16:16,159
Yes, I saw her near the river.

929
01:16:17,479 --> 01:16:18,399
Thank you.

930
01:16:18,479 --> 01:16:19,319
Let's go, Tofu.

931
01:16:47,279 --> 01:16:48,359
-Mom.
-Mrs. Na.

932
01:16:50,920 --> 01:16:51,880
I'm sorry.

933
01:16:57,439 --> 01:16:58,439
Let's keep going.

934
01:17:31,279 --> 01:17:32,399
Excuse me.

935
01:17:32,479 --> 01:17:33,560
I…

936
01:17:34,119 --> 01:17:35,039
How can I help you?

937
01:17:36,439 --> 01:17:38,439
I want to go to…

938
01:17:40,319 --> 01:17:41,319
Where are you going?

939
01:17:47,479 --> 01:17:49,720
Are you here alone?

940
01:17:51,720 --> 01:17:54,079
Why don't you call a relative
to pick you up?

941
01:17:54,680 --> 01:17:56,439
I didn't bring my phone.

942
01:17:57,560 --> 01:17:58,720
In that case,

943
01:17:58,800 --> 01:18:00,520
shall I take you home?

944
01:18:00,600 --> 01:18:01,920
Where do you live?

945
01:18:09,720 --> 01:18:13,359
Someone brought her here
after finding her near the river.

946
01:18:13,880 --> 01:18:16,760
She said she's here
with her son named Nut and Tofu.

947
01:18:17,319 --> 01:18:18,880
I thought of you.

948
01:18:20,000 --> 01:18:22,279
I totally forgot about you.

949
01:18:23,119 --> 01:18:24,520
Unbelievable.

950
01:18:24,600 --> 01:18:26,760
You didn't think of your father
who's a cop.

951
01:18:26,840 --> 01:18:28,439
I didn't know

952
01:18:28,520 --> 01:18:30,439
he was your father.

953
01:18:30,520 --> 01:18:33,319
It's such a small world.

954
01:18:35,039 --> 01:18:35,920
Mom.

955
01:18:36,399 --> 01:18:37,960
How did you end up there?

956
01:18:42,800 --> 01:18:43,720
Nut.

957
01:18:44,479 --> 01:18:46,439
Why don't we talk at the hotel?

958
01:18:51,720 --> 01:18:52,560
Nut.

959
01:18:53,439 --> 01:18:54,319
Can we talk?

960
01:19:20,399 --> 01:19:21,920
Your mom said

961
01:19:22,720 --> 01:19:24,159
she suddenly lost her memory

962
01:19:24,920 --> 01:19:26,239
while taking a walk.

963
01:19:27,319 --> 01:19:29,960
She forgot where she was,
so she kept walking.

964
01:19:31,399 --> 01:19:34,880
The person who found her
also said she seemed strange.

965
01:19:34,960 --> 01:19:36,239
She sounded confused.

966
01:19:37,119 --> 01:19:38,720
She couldn't answer her.

967
01:19:40,079 --> 01:19:41,960
I think something is wrong with her.

968
01:19:43,640 --> 01:19:46,359
You should talk to your mom
to see what the problem is.

969
01:19:51,319 --> 01:19:52,439
I will, sir.

970
01:19:53,079 --> 01:19:53,920
Thank you so much.

971
01:20:03,840 --> 01:20:04,920
The reason you left…

972
01:20:07,239 --> 01:20:08,319
you weren't mad, right?

973
01:20:11,359 --> 01:20:12,880
Was there another reason?

974
01:20:54,000 --> 01:20:55,560
How long has this been happening?

975
01:21:04,840 --> 01:21:06,239
I don't know.

976
01:21:12,159 --> 01:21:14,359
I feel strange.

977
01:21:21,199 --> 01:21:22,159
I…

978
01:21:23,319 --> 01:21:25,439
I'm getting very forgetful, Nut.

979
01:21:31,119 --> 01:21:32,479
I forget…

980
01:21:35,239 --> 01:21:36,279
what I'm going to do.

981
01:21:39,880 --> 01:21:41,359
I forget

982
01:21:42,359 --> 01:21:43,840
what I've done.

983
01:21:48,640 --> 01:21:49,840
I forget days.

984
01:21:53,960 --> 01:21:55,279
I forget people's names.

985
01:21:57,239 --> 01:21:58,920
Sometimes, I forget

986
01:22:01,079 --> 01:22:02,760
what I want to say.

987
01:22:11,800 --> 01:22:13,279
I went to see the doctor.

988
01:22:16,159 --> 01:22:18,640
Dr. Kanya examined me.

989
01:22:25,039 --> 01:22:27,399
She said…

990
01:22:30,680 --> 01:22:32,119
I'm showing symptoms of…

991
01:22:35,159 --> 01:22:36,079
Alzheimer's.

992
01:22:45,000 --> 01:22:46,359
I'm sorry, Nut.

993
01:22:52,640 --> 01:22:53,680
It's okay, Mom.

994
01:24:02,119 --> 01:24:04,600
The truth is she has been
showing signs for a while.

995
01:24:07,159 --> 01:24:08,640
I didn't think much of them.

996
01:24:11,800 --> 01:24:12,800
These three, please.

997
01:24:14,760 --> 01:24:16,600
Didn't I just buy some last week?

998
01:24:17,319 --> 01:24:18,359
Why have we run out?

999
01:24:20,159 --> 01:24:22,479
Your mom has been feeding Kuenchai
a lot more often.

1000
01:24:22,960 --> 01:24:24,680
Some days she feeds him several times.

1001
01:24:30,119 --> 01:24:31,760
I'm a horrible son.

1002
01:24:46,800 --> 01:24:48,279
You've been working hard.

1003
01:24:50,079 --> 01:24:51,880
You've got a lot on your mind.

1004
01:24:54,359 --> 01:24:55,560
On the other hand,

1005
01:24:57,479 --> 01:24:59,119
it's my job to take care of her.

1006
01:25:01,560 --> 01:25:03,239
I've been with her the whole time.

1007
01:25:05,840 --> 01:25:07,560
I saw her abnormalities.

1008
01:25:16,239 --> 01:25:17,920
Did I already feed you?

1009
01:25:19,920 --> 01:25:21,760
Kuenchai, come and eat.

1010
01:25:25,319 --> 01:25:26,760
You already gave him his food.

1011
01:25:28,039 --> 01:25:29,279
Did I?

1012
01:25:39,319 --> 01:25:40,760
Are you looking for something?

1013
01:25:40,840 --> 01:25:42,680
I'm looking for the fruit knife.

1014
01:25:43,720 --> 01:25:45,439
I don't know where I put it.

1015
01:25:58,319 --> 01:26:00,119
I didn't suspect a thing.

1016
01:26:06,000 --> 01:26:07,399
I'm sorry, Nut.

1017
01:26:10,439 --> 01:26:11,920
Why is this happening?

1018
01:26:14,960 --> 01:26:16,640
Everything was getting better.

1019
01:26:19,159 --> 01:26:21,039
Our family was about to be happy.

1020
01:26:24,600 --> 01:26:26,119
Don't I deserve

1021
01:26:27,960 --> 01:26:29,479
to be happy?

1022
01:26:42,359 --> 01:26:43,840
Don't blame yourself.

1023
01:26:46,439 --> 01:26:48,119
No one is to blame here.

1024
01:26:52,640 --> 01:26:54,640
Since your mom is already sick,

1025
01:26:57,520 --> 01:26:59,960
why don't we find a way to help her?

1026
01:27:05,439 --> 01:27:06,760
This disease

1027
01:27:06,840 --> 01:27:08,279
can't be cured.

1028
01:27:10,720 --> 01:27:11,880
Soon…

1029
01:27:14,319 --> 01:27:15,720
she will forget you,

1030
01:27:17,960 --> 01:27:19,159
me,

1031
01:27:22,520 --> 01:27:24,079
and even herself.

1032
01:27:41,199 --> 01:27:42,840
Let's come up with a way

1033
01:27:45,399 --> 01:27:47,159
to take care of her

1034
01:27:50,199 --> 01:27:52,079
before she forgets everything.

1035
01:28:09,640 --> 01:28:10,720
Who do you suspect?

1036
01:28:10,800 --> 01:28:12,079
Tofu.

1037
01:28:12,159 --> 01:28:15,560
He could have been in the house that day
and saw the whole thing.

1038
01:28:16,159 --> 01:28:19,600
If you don't want
a twisted, tormented life like mine,

1039
01:28:20,079 --> 01:28:21,920
you'll have to live mindfully.

1040
01:28:23,159 --> 01:28:25,279
Correct your mistakes while you still can.

1041
01:28:25,920 --> 01:28:27,439
One person lost his memory.

1042
01:28:28,600 --> 01:28:30,000
Another person is losing hers.

1043
01:28:32,159 --> 01:28:33,159
Who knows?

1044
01:28:33,920 --> 01:28:36,000
I might remember something soon.

1045
01:28:39,279 --> 01:28:41,279
You've been doing a great job.

1046
01:28:45,479 --> 01:28:46,560
Don't blame yourself.

1047
01:28:49,640 --> 01:28:50,600
You did great.

